Today and next tuesday we will cover very useful topics.
As you all know, very soon the renju world championship will begin
you can read more information about WC from www.renju.ee/wc
that website is being updated now
and every day more information appears there
most of you never joined WC before
if you want to become a world champion, you need to get the right to play in AT.
do you know how to get to AT?
AT is the tournament where 12 strongest masters fight for the title of world champion.
the 12 seats are taken as follows:
the previous world champion will have personal place to next WC
the previous WC 2-6 places will give national places to next WC
meaning, for example in last WC, estonia had 3rd place in AT,
means, estonia gets 1 national seat for this coming WC
after having played the national qualification tournament,
we select best one, who will go to AT directly.
so, theses are first 7 seats in WC.
the remaining seats, 8-12 are taken through international qualification tournament (QT)
such QT is played 3 days before WC,
and 5 best players from that QT, will be lucky to play in AT
Most likely, your renju career will begin from QT
if you have the right to play in QT,
then it means, you are about to enter a very tough competition,
because QT is full of scary monsters :)
How many persons will play in QT this year?
what means "the right to play", can you detail please?
i suggest you all read this page later
it illustrates clearly, how to enter QT and AT
So, imagine, you are one of the people who will play in QT
(sooner or later it will be reality)
and your dream is to be among best 5 in QT, so that you could reach to AT,
you need to prepare well in order to make dream come true.
Today I will teach you, how to prepare for QT
how to make your chance to win as high as possible.
Many people go to QT and AT without preparation,
so their win depends on luck.
If you want to guarantee your success, you need lots of systematic preparation.
homework: play in QT, advanced homework, be in top 5 QT
What do you think, whats the first thing you do for preparation for QT?
decide one variant to analyse very carfully....
buy the ticket to go there, that's first, rest is done by force-majore
in a way, you are all correct,
of course, preparation can be divided into many aspects,
such as travel preparation, body and mind preparation (exercises) etc
but when we speak of renju,
the first thing is to find out who your opponents are.
you have to collect the list of QT players.

在给我上英文课 真晕
that may cause the top 5 score go up nearly by 0,5
QT has always even number of players
so, you need to plan 5,5 is safe
if you play with weak opponent, you dont need to prepare too hard
then you play your favorite variants, which you know well
but for strong opponents, be careful,
because its harder to beat them by your favorite variants, besides, they prepare against you too
a professional player can guess what you plan to play, even before game begins
in ORC, in renlib files, in database, everywhere
you should expect the unexpected, even from weak player, (if someone in that reach the QT can be called weak)
nearly every QT has offered some surprises
always some "black horse" gets among top 5
i hope, some of you will be next black horse

ok lets start knocking them down, 1 by 1
hui, if you need to prepare against sushkov,
He will join Meijinsen for the firsttime this year.
how do you find out, what he plays?
hui, do you know how many points he got in AT 2001?
and hui, you must beat him!
you will not qualify to AT
if you really wish to reach to AT,
you must be ready in your heart
ok, let me ask others then
who is ready to beat sushkov today?
we are ready in our heart, but our mind doesn't want to follow
i mean not by skill, but by heart
means, you are ready to face him, challenge him,
and not be secared to death
because if your heart is not ready, then no matter how you prepare, its no use
we choose you, to beat Sushkov and others in QT.
first tell us, what is your favorite opening?
i can beat sushkov, and all, and ando too !!
he is thinking... does he swap?
someone say if you can play i1 then you can play everythind
but he doesnt hurry with white stone
first, he thinks, what is konjin's plan
konjin expects classic i1 opening with 4-h10..
i guess he will spend about 5 minutes here
all newcomers tend to play fast
because he is lacking real confidence,
so he plays fast moves, to "imitate confidence"
and actually thereby ruins his game
som konjin will play super fast,
he he, and he lose slowly !
you dont need to "show off" by playing fast
so you dont need to prove it by being fast
as you know, Kawamura, also a world champion, got 9 from 11 in AT
i don't know theory, if he switch to d3, my spirit is gone :D
you must not only think of your ideas
there are hundreds of sushkovs games
if he has almost no i1 games there,
then he will likely transfer to d3
will he choose black or white?
sushkov might like both colors here
and sushkov has 0 games in i1!!
means, i am most certain, he doesnt want to take risk in important QT,
oh! so he will transfer to d3?
and hopes to overplay you "safely" in d3
because he has no experience in i1
and its foolish to make i1 experiment in such an important tournament
then you cannot be sure if he swaps or not
then i will play 9-k10, from GM killer21
but from i1->d3, you are sure he will be white
so that will make your preparation much easier -
you only need to prepare yourself as black in d3
such method would not work, if sushkov had i1 experience
but since he doesnt have i1 experience, he will surely transfer to d3
tell me, if the game is draw,
so he will try to win, at any cost
if he get only draw against me (unknown player) then he is gone
meaning, you dont have to take risks here
remember! in sharp and complex variants, he is much better counter
he will surely beat you by skil
so if you go to wild attack,
better strategy is: you dont go for win, if you are sure your opponent self needs win very much.
and he will make crazy risks,
and there will be your win opportunity, when he gambles!
he will make an aggressive move at some moment,
and he prays that you will be scared,
but if you are clever enough to sense this moment,
and you dont "believe him", and you seek for your own win now,
if you try to win in opening, its impossible.
he knows theory much better than you, he counts more steps ahead than you, he knows all the tactics better, etc.
his only weakness is "he needs win!"
and if you use his weakness well,
you may have a chance to beat him
another 5 could help black force draw situation
so, we have predicted game until here.
now big question to everybody - where is sushkov's 6th move?? (you can check databases and all)
if i have not the databases,how can i do ?
sushkov likes only 1 kind of 6th here
next week when we have less
everybody tells me, who found what
ok i help you this time
the database from 2004 is free to download on a japanese site, use google.
databases prove, that sushkov plays only 6-k10
he has about 10 games in this way as white,
so that helps your preparation, right?
so, dont only prepare what "you know" but what "he plays"
if you will be surprised by this 6th move,
means, you didnt do your home preparation
if you want to get top 5 in QT
then you must KNOW that sushkov will play 6-k10
i would not be particulary surprised, because it is one of the 3-4 continuations
but i will be anyhow in little trouble
but in order to be prepared,
you need to know what he plays
because its impossible to prepare for all theory
i would play k9 or g9
remember - the strategy is draw game!
try to find the safe positional way, not sharp game
if you give up this tactics,
and still go sharp, then you die
Which variant here gives most safe and balance play for black??

any activity is suicide for white
if you defend! what can happen?
you defend as long as necessary
for example, you have win in upper,
but white VCF will break it
so if white VCF is cut at some time,
then you will have real win chance
if it is getting too complicate i will lose
i would try to play closer
even 9, i don't know if i would play it
this is a good trap situation
you gave up attack on top
now he is certain you gave up all attack thoughts
and now, his defense vcf is gone
this is the tactics - your 17 and 19 show to him that you are ready to balance game
corretly playing, he should care your attack
and he will have trouble to win later
and play to i6 or other
important is, dont push to win from opening, but let him try win,
when he gambles, you bite him
because all masters need some gamble at some point, to make draw game become win
if you sense the gamble moment,
so you imagine, this is your game with him
same way, you prepare 4-5 more scenarios against him
And you prepare same way against all QT players,
Your advantage is - nobody knows about you
its more difficult for me to prepare - they all know a lot about me
about my style, about my openings
and they all are sitting there now, and digging in theory against me

But I think it is difficult to predict your move!
